bayStackRadiusMib.name: bayStackRadiusMib

revisions.description: Ver 14: Added bsRadiusReachabilityTimeout bsRadiusReachabilityRetry bsRadiusReachabilityBadTimer bsRadiusReachabilityGoodTimer .
Ver 12: Added notification types for reachability up/down.
Ver 11: Added additional radius server settings.
Ver 6: Added bsRadiusDynAuthClientReplayProtection Added bsRadiusAccountingInterimUpdates and bsRadiusAccountingInterimUpdatesInterval.
Ver 2: Added support for RADIUS requests servers.

bayStackRadiusMib.description: This MIB module is used for RADIUS configuration settings in Nortel's software and products.

bsRadiusUseMgmtIp.name: bsRadiusUseMgmtIp
bsRadiusUseMgmtIp.description: This object controls whether RADIUS uses the system's management IP address as the source address for RADIUS requests.

bsRadiusAccountingEnabled.name: bsRadiusAccountingEnabled
bsRadiusAccountingEnabled.description: This object controls whether RADIUS accounting is enabled.

bsRadiusPasswordFallbackEnabled.name: bsRadiusPasswordFallbackEnabled
bsRadiusPasswordFallbackEnabled.description: This object controls whether RADIUS password fallback is enabled.

bsRadiusAccountingPort.name: bsRadiusAccountingPort
bsRadiusAccountingPort.description: This object controls the port used for RADIUS accounting.

bsRadiusAccountingInterimUpdates.name: bsRadiusAccountingInterimUpdates
bsRadiusAccountingInterimUpdates.description: This object controls whether RADIUS interim updates are enabled or disabled.

bsRadiusAccountingInterimUpdatesInterval.name: bsRadiusAccountingInterimUpdatesInterval
bsRadiusAccountingInterimUpdatesInterval.description: This object controls the interval for RADIUS interim updates.

bsRadiusAccountingInterimUpdatesInterval.name: bsRadiusAccountingInterimUpdatesIntervalSource
bsRadiusAccountingInterimUpdatesInterval.description: This object controls the source for the interval value for RADIUS interim updates. If the value is configuredValue(1), then the value of bsRadiusAccountingInterimUpdatesInterval is used. If the value is radiusServer(2), then a value obtained from the RADIUS server is used.

bsRadiusDynAuthReplayProtection.name: bsRadiusDynAuthReplayProtection
bsRadiusDynAuthReplayProtection.description: Globally enable or disable RADIUS replay protection.

bsRadiusReachability.name: bsRadiusReachability
bsRadiusReachability.description: Select the method used to test RADIUS server reachablity.

bsRadiusReachabilityUserName.name: bsRadiusReachabilityUserName
bsRadiusReachabilityUserName.description: The username used for the RADIUS server reachability useRadius option.

bsRadiusReachabilityPassword.name: bsRadiusReachabilityPassword
bsRadiusReachabilityPassword.description: The password used for the RADIUS server reachability useRadius option.

bsRadiusEncapsulationProtocol.name: bsRadiusEncapsulationProtocol
bsRadiusEncapsulationProtocol.description: This object specifies the type of encapsulation for RADIUS packets.

bsRadiusReachabilityTimeout.name: bsRadiusReachabilityTimeout
bsRadiusReachabilityTimeout.description: This object specifies the time interval to wait before re-sending a message to the RADIUS server .

bsRadiusReachabilityRetry.name: bsRadiusReachabilityRetry
bsRadiusReachabilityRetry.description: This object specifies the number of retry attempts to reach the RADIUS server.

bsRadiusReachabilityBadTimer.name: bsRadiusReachabilityBadTimer
bsRadiusReachabilityBadTimer.description: This object specifies the interval between checks when the RADIUS server is unreachable.

bsRadiusReachabilityGoodTimer.name: bsRadiusReachabilityGoodTimer
bsRadiusReachabilityGoodTimer.description: This object specifies the interval between checks when the RADIUS server is reachable.

bsRadiusServerTable.name: bsRadiusServerTable
bsRadiusServerTable.description: This table is used to control RADIUS server settings.

bsRadiusServerEntry.name: bsRadiusServerEntry
bsRadiusServerEntry.description: An entry containing objects defining how to connect to a RADIUS server.

bsRadiusServerIndex.name: bsRadiusServerIndex
bsRadiusServerIndex.description: A unique integer value used to identify entries in this table.

bsRadiusServerPriority.name: bsRadiusServerPriority
bsRadiusServerPriority.description: This value indicates the order in which entries in this table are used when attempting to contact a RADIUS server. Entries with a lower priority number are tried first. If two entries have the same priority value, the entry with a lower index value is tried first. Also note that entries which contain an invalid internet address will not be used.

bsRadiusServerAddressType.name: bsRadiusServerAddressType
bsRadiusServerAddressType.description: The type of address contained in the corresponding instance of bsRadiusServerAddress.

bsRadiusServerAddress.name: bsRadiusServerAddress
bsRadiusServerAddress.description: The internet address to use when attempting to contact a RADIUS server.

bsRadiusServerUdpPort.name: bsRadiusServerUdpPort
bsRadiusServerUdpPort.description: The UDP port number to use when trying to contact the RADIUS server at the address contained in the corresponding instance of bsRadiusServerAddress.

bsRadiusServerTimeout.name: bsRadiusServerTimeout
bsRadiusServerTimeout.description: The time interval to wait before re-sending a message to this RADIUS server.

bsRadiusServerSecret.name: bsRadiusServerSecret
bsRadiusServerSecret.description: The shared RADIUS secret to use when communicating with the RADIUS server. Note that when this object is retrieved, its value will always by a zero-length octet string.

bsRadiusServerRowStatus.name: bsRadiusServerRowStatus
bsRadiusServerRowStatus.description: Controls row creation/deletion in this table.

bsRadiusServerAccountingPort.name: bsRadiusServerAccountingPort
bsRadiusServerAccountingPort.description: The UDP accounting port number to use when trying to contact the RADIUS server at the address contained in the corresponding instance of bsRadiusServerAddress.

bsRadiusServerAccountingEnabled.name: bsRadiusServerAccountingEnabled
bsRadiusServerAccountingEnabled.description: This object controls whether RADIUS accounting is enabled for this RADIUS server instance.

bsRadiusServerRetryLimit.name: bsRadiusServerRetryLimit
bsRadiusServerRetryLimit.description: This object specifies the number of RADIUS retry attempts, for this RADIUS server instance.

bsRadiusDynAuthClientTable.name: bsRadiusDynAuthClientTable
bsRadiusDynAuthClientTable.description: This table is used to configure RADIUS Dynamic Authorization Clients. RADIUS Dynamic Authorization Clients are entities which can send Disconnect and Change Of Authorization requests to a RADIUS Dynamic Authorization Server.

bsRadiusDynAuthClientEntry.name: bsRadiusDynAuthClientEntry
bsRadiusDynAuthClientEntry.description: An entry containing objects defining RADIUS Dynamic Authorization Clients which can connect to this RADIUS Dynamic Authorization Server.

bsRadiusDynAuthClientAddressType.name: bsRadiusDynAuthClientAddressType
bsRadiusDynAuthClientAddressType.description: The type of address contained in the corresponding instance of bsRadiusDynAuthClientAddress.

bsRadiusDynAuthClientAddress.name: bsRadiusDynAuthClientAddress
bsRadiusDynAuthClientAddress.description: The internet address of a RADIUS Dynamic Authorization Client configured in this entry.

bsRadiusDynAuthClientUdpPort.name: bsRadiusDynAuthClientUdpPort
bsRadiusDynAuthClientUdpPort.description: The UDP port number the server/NAS listens on for requests from the RADIUS Dynamic Authorization Client configured in this entry.

bsRadiusDynAuthClientSecret.name: bsRadiusDynAuthClientSecret
bsRadiusDynAuthClientSecret.description: The secret shared between RADIUS Dynamic Authorization Client and Server. Note that when this object is retrieved, its value will always by a zero-length octet string.

bsRadiusDynAuthClientEnabled.name: bsRadiusDynAuthClientEnabled
bsRadiusDynAuthClientEnabled.description: Enable or disable packet receive from this RADIUS Dynamic Authorization Client. The NAS will not listen for requests from the client unless this object is true(1).

bsRadiusDynAuthClientProcessDisconnectRe.name: bsRadiusDynAuthClientProcessDisconnectRequests
bsRadiusDynAuthClientProcessDisconnectRe.description: Enable or disable processing of Disconnect requests from the RADIUS Dynamic Authorization Client.

bsRadiusDynAuthClientProcessCoARequests.name: bsRadiusDynAuthClientProcessCoARequests
bsRadiusDynAuthClientProcessCoARequests.description: Enable or disable processing of Change-Of-Authorization requests from the RADIUS Dynamic Authorization Client.

bsRadiusDynAuthClientRowStatus.name: bsRadiusDynAuthClientRowStatus
bsRadiusDynAuthClientRowStatus.description: Controls row creation/deletion in this table.

bsRadiusDynAuthClientReplayProtection.name: bsRadiusDynAuthClientReplayProtection
bsRadiusDynAuthClientReplayProtection.description: Enable or disable RADIUS replay protection.

bsRadiusDynAuthClientProcessReAuthReques.name: bsRadiusDynAuthClientProcessReAuthRequests
bsRadiusDynAuthClientProcessReAuthReques.description: Enable or disable the processing of Reauthentication requests from the RADIUS Dynamic Authorization Client.

bsRadiusExtDynAuthClientTable.name: bsRadiusExtDynAuthClientTable
bsRadiusExtDynAuthClientTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the RADIUS Dynamic Authorization Clients with which the server shares a secret. This is an extension of radiusDynAuthClientTable.

bsRadiusExtDynAuthClientEntry.name: bsRadiusExtDynAuthClientEntry
bsRadiusExtDynAuthClientEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing one Dynamic Authorization Client with which the server shares a secret.

bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcRequests.name: bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcRequests
bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcRequests.description: The number of RADIUS Reauthentication-requests received from this Dynamic Authorization Client. This also includes the Reauthentication requests that have a Service-Type attribute with value 'Authorize Only'. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the DAS module (re)starts, as indicated by the value of radiusDynAuthServerCounterDiscontinuity.

bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcAuthOnlyRequests.name: bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcAuthOnlyRequests
bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcAuthOnlyRequests.description: The number of RADIUS Reauthentication-requests that include a Service-Type attribute with value 'Authorize Only' received from this Dynamic Authorization Client. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the DAS module (re)starts, as indicated by the value of radiusDynAuthServerCounterDiscontinuity.

bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcDupRequests.name: bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcDupRequests
bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcDupRequests.description: The number of duplicate RADIUS Reauthentication-Request packets received from this Dynamic Authorization Client. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the DAS module (re)starts, as indicated by the value of radiusDynAuthServerCounterDiscontinuity.

bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcAcks.name: bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcAcks
bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcAcks.description: The number of incoming Reauthentication packets from this Dynamic Authorization Client silently discarded by the server application for some reason other than malformed, bad authenticators, or unknown types. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the DAS module (re)starts, as indicated by the value of radiusDynAuthServerCounterDiscontinuity.

bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcNacks.name: bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcNacks
bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcNacks.description: The number of RADIUS Reauthentication-NAK packets sent to this Dynamic Authorization Client. This includes the RADIUS Reauthentication-NAK packets sent with a Service-Type attribute with value 'Authorize Only' and the RADIUS Reauthentication-NAK packets sent because no session context was found. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the DAS module (re)starts, as indicated by the value of radiusDynAuthServerCounterDiscontinuity.

bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcNacksAuthOnlyReq.name: bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcNacksAuthOnlyRequests
bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcNacksAuthOnlyReq.description: The number of RADIUS Reauthentication-NAK packets that include a Service-Type attribute with value 'Authorize Only' sent to this Dynamic Authorization Client. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the DAS module (re)starts, as indicated by the value of radiusDynAuthServerCounterDiscontinuity.

bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcNacksNoSess.name: bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcNacksNoSess
bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcNacksNoSess.description: The number of RADIUS Reauthentication-NAK packets sent to this Dynamic Authorization Client because no session context was found. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the DAS module (re)starts, as indicated by the value of radiusDynAuthServerCounterDiscontinuity.

bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcSessReauthentica.name: bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcSessReauthenticated
bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcSessReauthentica.description: The number of user sessions reauthenticated for the Reauthentication-Requests received from this Dynamic Authorization Client. Depending on site- specific policies, a single Reauthentication request can change multiple user sessions' authorization. In cases where this Dynamic Authorization Server has no knowledge of the number of user sessions that are affected by a single request, each such CoA-Request will count as a single affected user session only. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the DAS module (re)starts, as indicated by the value of radiusDynAuthServerCounterDiscontinuity.

bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcMalformed.name: bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcMalformed
bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcMalformed.description: The number of malformed RADIUS Reauthentication-Request packets received from this Dynamic Authorization Client. Bad authenticators and unknown types are not included as malformed Reauthentication-Requests. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the DAS module (re)starts, as indicated by the value of radiusDynAuthServerCounterDiscontinuity.

bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcDropped.name: bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcDropped
bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcDropped.description: The number of incoming Reauthentication packets from this Dynamic Authorization Client silently discarded by the server application for some reason other than malformed, bad authenticators, or unknown types. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the DAS module (re)starts, as indicated by the value of radiusDynAuthServerCounterDiscontinuity.

bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcBadAuths.name: bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcBadAuths
bsRadiusExtDynAuthServRcBadAuths.description: The number of RADIUS Reauthentication-Request packets that contained an invalid Authenticator field received from this Dynamic Authorization Client. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the DAS module (re)starts, as indicated by the value of radiusDynAuthServerCounterDiscontinuity.

bsRadiusReachabilityServerDown.name: bsRadiusReachabilityServerDown
bsRadiusReachabilityServerDown.description: This notification is generated when a Radius server fails to respond to reachability requests.

bsRadiusReachabilityServerUp.name: bsRadiusReachabilityServerUp
bsRadiusReachabilityServerUp.description: This notification is generated when a Radius server, which has previously failed to respond to reachability requests, responds to a reachability request.
